Canada strongly condemned the recent suicide attack in Israel, emphasizing the importance of maintaining the Middle East peace process.
The incident involved two suicide bombers, one killed in the blast and the other by police.
The attackers were linked to various militant groups, sparking concerns about border security.
The Palestinian Authority and Hamas also denounced the violence.
Israeli officials expressed fears of further infiltrations from Gaza.
The attack reignited tensions, prompting calls for increased security measures.
France urged continued peace efforts despite the tragic event.
The incident highlighted ongoing challenges in the region's conflict.
